-- Brunei Ruler Buys 20% Stake in Turkey’s Yildiz Unit Marsa
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-03-20T07:33:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/brunei-ruler-buys-20-stake-in-turkey-s-yildiz-unit-marsa.html
Brunei Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah
bought a 20 percent stake in Turkish Yildiz Holding AS’s
margarine and vegetable oil producer Marsa Yag, Yildiz said
today in a statement.  Yildiz, the maker of Godiva chocolates, also set up a joint
venture named Western Food and Packaging SDN BHD in Brunei with
a $30 million capital, according to an emailed statement from
the Istanbul-based company.  The total value of the partnerships including the stake
sale and the establishment of the new joint venture is $100
million, it said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
